def_cn: 盎格鲁-撒克逊的（指英国从公元5世纪至1066年诺曼征服这段时期）
def_en: The Anglo-Saxon period is the period of English history from the fifth century A.D. to the Norman Conquest in 1066.

def_cn: 盎格鲁-撒克逊族的;英国血统的
def_en: Anglo-Saxon people are members of or are descended from the English race.
Anglo-Saxon attitudes or ideas have been strongly influenced by English culture.

def_cn: （指英格兰自公元5世纪至1066年诺曼征服这段时期的）盎格鲁-撒克逊语，古英语
def_en: Anglo-Saxon is the language that was spoken in England between the fifth century A.D. and the Norman Conquest in 1066.
